                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-168-victim1379 t18320517-168-viclabel986"></join>. On the 26th of April I placed my great coat in a chaise, in his coach-house, about seven o'clock in the morning - I missed it at eight, and saw it afterwards in possession of the officer.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he had bought the coat of two men in Hackney-fields.</p>
